title: For Sale:  Sig Sauer P229 Blue Piranha 9mm
postcontent: Sig Sauer P229 Blue Piranha 9mmBuy it online at www.copsgunshop.net.  All FFL rules and regs apply.  Buyer pays shipping or sales tax.  Sorry, no trades.   This pistol is BNIB and came to us in a trade.  It was an exclusive pistol distributed by Lew Horton Distribution and is no longer in production.  Custom leather right hand holster and mag pouch included, as seen in the pic.  SIG Sauer’s P229 has planted some impressive milestones in its time. In addition to being widely utilized by federal, state and municipal law enforcement agencies, it is also the handgun that has significance in the history of the company itself. In particular, the P229 was the first pistol SIG manufactured in America, when the company opened its plant in New Hampshire. Until then, the German/Swiss gun maker imported all its firearm to the American market. Now, for a limited time, Lew Horton Distributing is offering a version of the double/single-action pistol as unique as its background. The Massachusetts wholesaler is selling its final order of Special Edition SIG P229 Blue Piranha. The Horton exclusive features a striking slide, finished in a bright blue PVD finish. And while this process gives the P229 a glossy and classic look, the finish does more than just add glitz. PVD (Physical Vapor Deposition) is able to deliver a harder and more corrosion-resistant coating than most other processes used today. In addition to the eye-catching finish, the Blue Piranha version of the SIG P229 also features G-10 Piranha Grips. From there, the pistol shares features common to this model of SIG. These include: front and rear cocking serrations, 3.9-inch barrel, SIGLITE night sights and an accessory rail. The Horton exclusive is available only in 9mm, though SIG does offer the P229 in two other calibers — .40S&W and .357SIG. Production of the Blue Piranha was limited to 500 units. The pistols ship with two 15-round magazines and have an MSRP of $1,299.  Sig Sauer P229 Blue Piranha 9mm

All were on my rotation so would typically be worn 4-5 times per month at most, all were purchased this year. For full watch functions, details, movements, just google the model numbers. Too much info to list and its already easily available on the internet. More pictures available to interested parties upon request.$300 cash. Seiko automatic SRPA82K1 also know as a Baby Tuna, nothing baby about it though. Comes complete with box, booklets, original rubber strap (some scrapes on the gold keeper) and a nice heavy aftermarket black steel bracelet (some scrapes on the bracelet but nothing major). The bracelet comes with all of the original links included, currently sized for a 7" wrist. This is a large watch at almost 52mm but since the lugs are built into the case itself it wears very comfortably on the wrist, I like big watches and have no issues whatsoever pulling this off on my medium sized 7" wrist. The heavy steel bracelet helps to counter balance the watch so it doesn't sit lop sided either. Selling because I also bought the stainless version and decided to keep that one instead. $150 cash. Casio G-Shock GW9400-3CR Rangeman. Very cool digital watch thats built for anything you can possibly throw at it. Has atomic time keeping (sets itself to correct time every night) and is solar powered so you never need to replace the battery. The negative display is neat and easy to read during the day, not as legible at night but thats why it has a light button and is solar powered so you dont have to worry about running your battery dry. Bought another all purpose "G" so dont wear this one as much anymore. Comes complete with original boxes and booklets, no scrapes on the crystal. Some scratches on the steel keeper and maybe a ding or two on the case, still looks almost new.$160 cash. Heimdallr, Sharkey v2.0, Sea Shepherd, SBBN015 Homage (copy) watch. This is a basically a very nice copy of the Seiko Tuna, watch is made out of stainless steel, has a domed AR coated sapphire crystal and runs on an automatic NH35 movement which is made by Seiko. The attention to detail is excellent, everything is aligned very well (which I cant say about any of my Seikos :) and it keeps good time. Comes with the box, basic bracelet tool and 1 extra link for the bracelet. The steel band on this runs a bit small and I only had to remove the one link to get a loose fit on my 7" wrist. Bought it for fun and just to see if I like the original Tuna design.
